descript.abstract:
Last updated 06 APRIL 2012 A route system depicting all roads within or in close proximity to an administrative unit.
A road is a motor vehicle travel way over 50 inches wide, unless classified and managed as a trail. Roads that are classified as Forest Roads shall be included in the layer. Forest roads are those roads that are wholly or partly within or adjacent to and serving the National Forest System that the Forest Service determines is necessary for the protection, administration, and utilization of the National Forest System and the use and development of its resources (36 CFR 212.1). Typically this includes all National Forest System Roads, County/State/or other roads managed by public road agencies that provide access to National Forest System lands. The layer may also contain, but is not required, locations of Unauthorized Roads (A road that is not a forest road or trail or a temporary road or trail and that is not included in a forest transportation atlas), Temporary Roads (A road necessary for emergency operations or authorized by contract, permit, lease, or other written authorization that is not a forest road or trail and that is not included in a forest transportation atlas), and/or private roads if they are needed for resource analysis or display. Route measurements and route directions must correspond to those stored in the Infra Oracle table RTE_BASICS.
descript.purpose: To provide analysis for U.S. Forest Service GIS and engineering applications. This feature class provides tools to retrieve information pertaining to road status within the Plumas National Forest boundary.

Geospatial Interface Visualization: HelpId: 690 DistributedIndicator: Y ProcessId: e30193a9-b312-4544-a751-a16764ccb365 ProcessName: Roads with Core Attributes RSW OwnerName: GI CO-OP Registry: GI COOPERATION ProcessType: Visualization Purpose: This vis connects your routed roads layer to the ii_road_core IWeb table. This table is on a nightly refresh cycle. This means the route information coming out of INFRA is one day old. Specific roads may be updated in this table in real time if you use the "Push to Road Core" button on the Oracle Forms editing form. The Road routes from your forests ROAD feature class are current per the default version.
PreRequisites: Runs on a GIS road layer that matches the 2008 Data Dictionary Standard. The road layer must have rte_cn populated so it will join to IWeb data. Results: The output layer will be added to your ArcMap project and will be named RoadsWithCoreAttributesRSW. Once the output layer is created you can apply additional visualizations by highlighting the RoadsWithCoreAttributesRSW layer and clicking the visualization button.
